HEADWORD: Rynd
<hw>Rynd</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A piece of iron crossing the hole in the upper
millstone by which the stone is supported on the spindle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

